d her work, the book gives readers a more accurate sense of the past and better prepares them for thinking and acting in the present.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnvironmentalismzUnited StatesxHistory. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311066767740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096515740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520965157423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520965157/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles